{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Anchialus Glacier | other_name = | photo = Sentinel-Range-location-map.png | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Location of Sentinel Range in Western Antarctica | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Anchialus Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = tributary | location = [[Ellsworth Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|77|51|50|S|85|24|30|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = {{convert|5|nmi|0|abbr=on}} | width = {{convert|2|nmi|0|abbr=on}} | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Sentinel Range]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
[[File:Northern-Sentinel-Map.jpg|thumb|280px|Map of northern Sentinel Range.]] '''Anchialus Glacier''' ({{lang-bg|italic=yes|ледник Анхиало}}, 'Lednik Anchialus' \'led-nik an-hi-'a-lo\) is the 8.5&nbsp;km long and 3.4&nbsp;km wide glacier in [[Sostra Heights]] on the east side of northern [[Sentinel Range]] in [[Ellsworth Mountains]], [[Antarctica]]. It is situated north of lower [[Embree Glacier]], east of [[Sabazios Glacier]], south of lower [[Newcomer Glacier]] and northwest of [[Vit Ice Piedmont]]. The glacier drains the northeast slopes of [[Mount Malone]] and the west slopes of [[Bracken Peak]], flows northwards and joins Newcomer Glacier east of [[Mount Lanning]].
The glacier is named after the ancient town of [[Pomorie#Ancient Greek colony and Roman centre|Anchialus]] in Southeastern Bulgaria.
==Location== Anchialus Glacier is centred at {{coord|77|51|50|S|85|24|30|W|display=inline,title}}. US mapping in 1961.
