'''Equine herpesvirus 9''' (EHV-9) is a [[virus]] of the family [[Herpesviridae]] that isolated from a case of epizootic encephalitis in a herd of [[Thomson's gazelle]] (Gazella thomsoni) in 1993.  Fatal encephalitis was reported from Thomson's gazelle, [[Giraffe]], and [[Polar bear]] <ref name=Donovan_2009>{{cite journal |vauthors=Donovan TA, Schrenzel MD, Tucker T, Pessier AP, Bicknese B, Busch MD, Wise AG, Maes R, Kiupel M, McKnight C, Nordhausen RW |title=Meningoencephalitis in a polar bear caused by equine herpesvirus 9 (EHV-9) |journal=Vet. Pathol. |volume=46 |issue=6 |pages=1138–43 |year=2009 |pmid=19605910 |doi=10.1354/vp.09-VP-0007-D-CR |url=http://journals.sagepub.com/doi/abs/10.1354/vp.09-VP-0007-D-CR}}</ref>   in natural infections. The virus was reported in an aborted [[Persian onager]] and a [[polar bear]].<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Schrenzel MD, Tucker TA, Donovan TA, Busch MD, Wise AG, Maes RK, Kiupel M |title=New hosts for equine herpesvirus 9 |journal=Emerging Infect. Dis. |volume=14 |issue=10 |pages=1616–9 |year=2008 |pmid=18826828 |pmc=2609862 |doi=10.3201/eid1410.080703 |url=http://wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/article/14/10/08-0703_article.htm}}</ref>

