{{italic title}}
{{notability|date=June 2016}}

'''''Problems in General Physics''''' is a book written by [[Igor Irodov]] and first published in 1981. It is a collection of about 2000 physics problems in [[mechanics]], [[thermodynamics]], [[molecular physics]], [[oscillation]]s, and [[electromagnetism]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/IrodovProblemsInGeneralPhysics|title=Problems in General Physics|last=I. E. Irodov|date=1988-01-01|publisher=Mir Publishers}}</ref> In India, the book is widely used by high school students preparing for engineering entrance examinations such as the [[Joint Entrance Examination]]. Each problem in the book is really unique, especially mechanics problems, and the questions help students understand the basic laws of physics. 

